bdf80466-10e2-4bdf-822f-54d34803e7be	9d557bd3-d799-4455-9dea-d87a5ebb08af	Human_Upgrade_Test_Bloodwork_Scenarios.pdf	/home/runner/workspace/uploads/1768680811140-306223980-Human_Upgrade_Test_Bloodwork_Scenarios.pdf	4441	2	2026-01-17 20:13:31.143443	completed	Human Upgrade – Test Bloodwork Scenarios\nThis document contains fully fictional, medically realistic bloodwork scenarios created solely for\ntesting the Human Upgrade application logic, alerts, and guardrails. These examples are not\nmedical advice.\nScenario A – Low Testosterone (TRT Evaluation Case)\nMale, 34 years old. Symptoms include fatigue, low libido, and low motivation. Pre-TRT evaluation.\nMarker Value Unit Reference Flag\nTotal Testosterone 6.2 nmol/L 10–30 LOW\nFree Testosterone 145 pmol/L 220–600 LOW\nSHBG 48 nmol/L 10–57 Normal\nLH 2.1 IU/L 1.7–8.6 Low-normal\nFSH 2.4 IU/L 1.5–12 Normal\nEstradiol (E2) 55 pmol/L 40–160 Normal\nHematocrit 43 % 40–50 Normal\nHemoglobin 14.5 g/dL 13.5–17.5 Normal\nLDL 142 mg/dL <100 HIGH\nTriglycerides 165 mg/dL <150 HIGH\nExpected App Behavior: Flag low testosterone values, recommend medical evaluation, and provide\nlifestyle-focused guidance without prescribing treatment.\nScenario B – On-TRT Critical Risk Case\nMale, 38 years old. On TRT for 9 months. Symptoms include headaches and shortness of breath.\nMarker Value Unit Reference Flag\nTotal Testosterone 31.5 nmol/L 10–30 HIGH\nFree Testosterone 780 pmol/L 220–600 HIGH\nEstradiol (E2) 185 pmol/L 40–160 HIGH\nHematocrit 56 % 40–50 CRITICAL\nHemoglobin 18.2 g/dL 13.5–17.5 HIGH\nRBC 6.4 x10^12/L 4.5–6.0 HIGH\nLDL 172 mg/dL <100 HIGH\nHDL 36 mg/dL >40 LOW\nTriglycerides 210 mg/dL <150 HIGH\nALT 52 U/L <45 HIGH\nExpected App Behavior: Trigger critical safety alerts, advise immediate medical consultation,\nhighlight cardiovascular and hematological risks without giving medical instructions.	f
